{%- comment -%}
  Loads the RewardsPro shared runtime:
    - `rp-shared.css` — loading/empty/error primitives reused by every widget
    - `rp-utils.js`   — `window.RPUtils` bag (sanitize/fetch/cache/escape)

  Every RewardsPro Liquid block must include this snippet at its top:

      {%- render 'rp_utils_loader' -%}

  The browser dedupes identical `src`/`href` URLs, so multiple widgets on the
  same page cost exactly one HTTP request per asset. The JS is synchronous on
  purpose — it's tiny (~4 KB) and widgets rely on `window.RPUtils` being
  defined at the moment their schema-injected <script> executes.
{%- endcomment -%}
<link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ 'rp-shared.css' | asset_url }}">
<script src="{{ 'rp-utils.js' | asset_url }}"></script>
